How cool is this?! 
The Playhouse It is designed by @abodaydesign and is located in Legok, Indonesia // Photos by Happy Lim. 
.
a home that lives up to its name. The two-storey house has a sculptural slider of concrete tucked in the corner; connecting the two floors in a playful way. If one prefer the stairs instead, the house of course also offers this option.

#architectsvision.
Swipe left! Dope or nope? 
La Iglesia de Tas The home is designed by @garmendiacorderoarquitectos + @tascareaga and is located in Sopuerta, Spain // Photos by @carlosgarmendia.
.
is an abandoned Renaissance church transformed into 190 sqm. of functionable home. Initially, the building was collapsed in its own interior with an alerting state of structural instability. However, the architect ensured to only intervene when there was no other alternative preserving as much of the old church as possible.

node.text:
#architectsvision 
Swipe left slowly to see the whole images!
MY. Residence / Design by @laneylainc 
visualization : @placesstudio / location: Manhattan Beach, #California 
-
“On a sloping 11,000 square foot lot, the design intent of this project was to craft a village of stone masses behind a quiet, landscaped wall.  From the curb, the facade feels both understated and timeless - a rooted monument from a time long gone. Yet its essence is communal. Inspired by mediterranean medinas, it is an experience that feels solitary and shared, a retreat and a relic.

Behind the front door, a sprawling sanctuary unfolds organized around large outdoor living spaces.  Its eroded beauty invites visitors to become immersed in the lush landscaping and serene stone corridors. Leveraging a minimal material palette, the home creates its own transformative context with a deeply rooted connection to nature” says architect Anthony Laney.

#architectsvision.
Who’d you bring? 
The Cosmos Villa The eco retreat is located in Soufriere, St Lucia // Video by @dreamworld.
.
A modernist eco villa positioned high on the hillside and cantilevered to embrace the panoramic views of the Caribbean Sea. The design of the villa has great emphasis on sustainability as it is powered by solar energy, rainwater is harvested and recycled, and the pool is purified with a salt water ozone system.

Meet DUNA at @lumacaststudio , its the newest addition premium fire features ! 
.
DUNA Inspired by sweeping and ever-changing landforms of the desert landscape, DUNA is a genuinely sensuous centerpiece for any outdoor space. The undulating top surface elicits a dynamic visual aesthetic from every angle while providing ample table space for entertaining.

DUNA is available in two sizes and a wide range of colors, making it a sculptural addition to your outdoor living and entertaining space.

node.text:
#architectsvision.
Describe this home in ONE word! 
The Belanda House The house is designed by 29 Design and is located in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia // Photos by Lin Ho.
.
a home where the experience of verticality trumps horizontality. The total of seven staircases threads the spaces together, and allows different experiences depending on which level you are on. The material palette was muted to contrast with the rich, emerald hues of the surrounding jungle.

#architectsvision 
Who’d you bring? 
The Hideout Horizon  @hideoutbali is (as indicated) located in the eastern part of Bali near the volcano, Mount Agung. // Photos by @thefreedomcomplex 
.
a truly magical off-grid eco bamboo home hidden in the Balinese jungles high up in the mountains of Gunung Agung volcano. Due to its remote location, it is situated far away from the city life and therefore perfect for adventurous souls. The all-bamboo house has two floors including a breezy outdoor living area with a hammock, a wardrobe, a bathroom, and a beautiful authentic pool.
